parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light is illuminated
the engine makes abnormal sounds
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the oil warning light is illuminated
the vehicle rattles
and the engine oil pressure is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive oil
the oil warning light is illuminated
the engine oil pressure is low
and the vehicle hesitates to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Stalling or loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine light is illuminated
the engine makes abnormal sounds
and the vehicle hesitates to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or unavailable recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle is included in a recall
but the parts for the repair are not available
or the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as jerking
lunging
or hesitation when shifting gears
loss of power
or failure to shift into gear. The check engine light may illuminate
and the vehicle may become stuck in a particular gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch assembly failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as a soft or spongy clutch pedal
the clutch pedal sticking to the floor
or the vehicle failing to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as a loud knocking noise
excessive oil consumption
loss of power during acceleration
or the check engine light illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal issues can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as excessive force needed to depress the brake pedal or the brake pedal feeling spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the worm gear shaft can cause the steering system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rubbing or whirring noise coming from the steering column
especially at low or stationary speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric steering system can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Noise coming from the steering wheel column
especially at low speeds
loss of steering control
and sudden failure of the steering system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Steering pulls to the right or left
unexpectedly and sporadically
noticeable by both drivers and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
RPM surging
and violent shaking of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Theft Due to Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the steering column can allow thieves to steal the vehicle, putting the public and law enforcement at risk.
symptoms: Theft of the vehicle due to the removal of the steering column cover and the use of a USB male end.
